idester looks toward a future “pregnant with the possibilities of new kinds of authenticity.”  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 4aComparative Religion. 4aReligion. 7aRELIGION / Comparative Religion.2bisacsh1 aChidester, David, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt0 cprintz978052024280740uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093824340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520938243423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520938243/original  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles